cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.CL

This paper deals with equational-based logics for proving properties of programming languages involving effects, which is a topic that falls under the scope of several computer science sub-categories. 

cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category as the paper presents a logical framework for reasoning about programming languages. 

cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely sub-category as the paper deals with properties of programming languages involving effects. 

cs.SE (Software Engineering) is another possible sub-category as the paper presents a method for proving properties of software systems. 

cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with equational-based logics for programming languages, which can be seen as formal languages. 

cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also a possible sub-category as the paper deals with computational effects arising from monads and comonads, which are concepts from functional programming that are related to natural language processing.
